REST API Design Best Practices
	1. Use Nouns for Resource Identification
	2. Use Plural Nouns to Name a Resource
	3. Use Proper HTTP Headers for Serialization Formats
	4. Get Method and Query Parameters Should Not Alter the State
	5. Use Sub-Resources for Relations
	6. Use Proper HTTP Methods
	7. HTTP Response Status Codes
	8. Field Name Casing Convention
	9. Searching, Sorting, Filtering, and Pagination
	10. Restful API Versioning
	11. Accept and respond with JSON
	12. Use nouns instead of verbs in endpoint paths
	13. Name collections with plural nouns
	14. Nesting resources for hierarchical objects
	15. Handle errors gracefully and return standard error codes
	16. Allow filtering, sorting, and pagination
	17. Maintain Good Security Practices
	18. Cache data to improve performance
    19. Versioning our APIs
